  "doc_id": "27519",
  "text": "Contrasting the linear reading of sect-to-church theory, research indicates manifold ambivalences in these transitions. First, sect-to-church transitions are neither unidirectional nor irreversible processes (cf. [CITATION_1] Stark and Finke 2000:259-276) : the same religious organizations can move the sect-to-church spectrum up and down at different moments in time, relaxing and increasing tension. Moreover, transition processes are not necessarily all-encompassing: religious organizations may relax specific characteristics while at the same time maintaining other boundaries with the environment (cf. Samuel H. Reimer 2009). [CITATION_2] Iannaccone ( :1203 has referred to this phenomenon as \"selective adaptation.\"",
